**Answer – about \(3\times10^{-1}\;{\rm W}\)**  

The acoustic intensity of a plane wave of pressure‑amplitude \(p^\prime\) in a medium of density \(\rho\) and speed of sound \(c\) is  

\[
I=\frac{(p^\prime)^2}{\rho\,c}
\]

The acoustic power that can be coupled to the gas in the tube is therefore  

\[
\dot{P}= I\,A,\qquad\text{with } A=\pi r^{2}\;.
\]

---

### Numerical values

* pressure amplitude  

\[
p^\prime=\frac{\Delta P}{2}
       =\frac{1.03\,{\rm MPa}-0.97\,{\rm MPa}}{2}
       =3.0\times10^{4}\ {\rm Pa}
\]

* density of argon (given)  

\[
\rho =1.78 \ {\rm kg\,m^{-3}}
\]

* speed of sound in argon  

\[
c = 3.23\times10^{2}\ {\rm m\,s^{-1}}
\]

* cross‑sectional area of the tube  

\[
A=\pi r^{2}
  =\pi(2.5\times10^{-4}\ {\rm m})^{2}
  \approx 1.96\times10^{-7}\ {\rm m^{2}}
\]

Now,

\[
I=\frac{(3.0\times10^{4}\ {\rm Pa})^{2}}
       {1.78\,{\rm kg\,m^{-3}}\; \times 323\,{\rm m\,s^{-1}}}
  \approx 1.57\times10^{6}\ {\rm W\,m^{-2}}
\]

\[
\dot{P}= I\,A
       \approx 1.57\times10^{6}\;{\rm W\,m^{-2}}
              \times 1.96\times10^{-7}\;{\rm m^{2}}
       \approx 3.07\times10^{-1}\ {\rm W}
\]

---

